.TH "start_poll_synchronize_srcu" 9 "start_poll_synchronize_srcu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
start_poll_synchronize_srcu \- Provide cookie and start grace period
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" start_poll_synchronize_srcu
.BI "(struct srcu_struct *ssp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ssp" 12
srcu_struct to provide cookie for.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function returns a cookie that can be passed to
\fBpoll_state_synchronize_srcu\fP, which will return true if a full grace
period has elapsed in the meantime.  Unlike \fBget_state_synchronize_srcu\fP,
this function also ensures that any needed SRCU grace period will be
started.  This convenience does come at a cost in terms of CPU overhead.
